# shadow-clerk: Web Meeting Minutes Assistant

Reads transcripts recorded and transcribed by clerk-daemon, and generates/updates meeting minutes (summary).

## Skill invocation name

shadow-clerk

## Instructions

The data directory is `{data_dir}`. The following files are stored there:
- Transcript files (default `transcript-YYYYMMDD.txt`, session `transcript-YYYYMMDDHHMM.txt`)
- Summary files (`summary-YYYYMMDD.md`, session `summary-YYYYMMDDHHMM.md`)
- Translation files (`transcript-YYYYMMDD-ja.txt`, etc.)
- `config.yaml` (configuration file)
- `words.txt`
- `glossary.txt` (glossary)
- `.clerk_session`, `.clerk_command`
- `.transcript_offset`
- Per-file translate offset files (`<transcript>.translate_offset`, e.g., `transcript-20260301.txt.translate_offset`)

If `output_directory` is set in `config.yaml`, transcript/summary/translation files are saved to that directory. Metadata files (`.clerk_session`, etc.) and `config.yaml` are always stored in the data directory.

### clerk-util command

Data directory access and process management are done via `{clerk_util_path}`.
clerk-util automatically references `output_directory` from `config.yaml`, resolving `transcript-*`/`summary-*` files from `output_directory` (or the data directory if not set). Just specify the filename for transparent access:

Data subcommands:
- `clerk-util read <file>` — Read a file
- `clerk-util write <file> <text>` — Write to a file
- `clerk-util append <file> <text>` — Append to a file
- `clerk-util lines <file>` — Show line count
- `clerk-util size <file>` — Show byte size
- `clerk-util mtime <file>` — Show last modified time
- `clerk-util exists <file>` — Check file existence
- `clerk-util ls` — List data directory contents
- `clerk-util command <cmd>` — Send command to clerk-daemon (writes to .clerk_command)
- `clerk-util recorder-status` — Show clerk-daemon status (`running` or `stopped`)
- `clerk-util read-config` — Read config.yaml to stdout (generates default if missing)
- `clerk-util write-config` — Write config.yaml from stdin
- `clerk-util write-config-value <key> <value>` — Update a specific key in config.yaml (`true`/`false`->bool, `null`->None, otherwise->string)
- `clerk-util path` — Print the full path of clerk-util

Process subcommands:
- `clerk-util poll-command <interval> [--timeout <sec>]` — Check `.clerk_command` every `<interval>` seconds. If a command is found, print it to stdout and exit. If `recorder-status` is `stopped`, print `stopped` and exit. With `--timeout`, return empty after `<sec>` seconds if no command found. Without `--timeout`, loop indefinitely
- `clerk-util start [opts]` — exec `clerk-daemon [opts]`
- `clerk-util stop` — Send SIGTERM to clerk-daemon process
- `clerk-util restart [opts]` — Stop clerk-daemon -> wait (max 10s) -> start (exec)
- `clerk-util run-llm <args...>` — exec llm_client

In the following instructions, `clerk-util` refers to its full path `{clerk_util_path}`.

### Subcommands

No arguments, or `update`:
- Run `clerk-util summarize --mode update`
- This automatically resolves the transcript file (from `.clerk_session` or today's date), checks `summary_source` config, and generates/updates minutes via `llm_client`

`full`:
- Run `clerk-util summarize --mode full`
- Same as `update` but regenerates minutes from the entire transcript

`summarize [DATE] [--mode full|update]`:
- DATE format: `YYYYMMDD` or `YYYYMMDDHHMM` (omit to auto-detect from session/today)
- Resolves transcript, translation, and summary file paths from the date
- Checks `summary_source` config to determine source file (transcript or translation)
- Runs `llm_client summarize` to generate minutes and save to summary file

`set language <lang>`:
- If `<lang>` is `ja` or `en`: run `clerk-util command set_language <lang>`
- If `<lang>` is `auto`: run `clerk-util command unset_language`
- Switches clerk-daemon's transcription language in real-time

`set model <size>`:
- Run `clerk-util command set_model <size>`
- `<size>` must be one of `tiny`, `base`, `small`, `medium`, `large-v3`
- Switches clerk-daemon's Whisper model in real-time (transcription pauses for ~10-30s during reload)

`config show`:
- Read current config with `clerk-util read-config` and display

`config set <key> <value>`:
- Run `clerk-util write-config-value <key> <value>`
- Display updated config with `clerk-util read-config`

`config init`:
- Generate default config file
- If config.yaml already exists, confirm before overwriting
- Running `clerk-util read-config` auto-generates default if file is missing

`start meeting`:
- Run `clerk-util command start_meeting`
- clerk-daemon creates a new session transcript file
- Translation offset is automatically managed per transcript file (clerk-daemon handles it via `<transcript>.translate_offset`)
- Read config with `clerk-util read-config`
- If `auto_translate: true`, start translation loop equivalent to `translate <translate_language>` (run same process as `translate <translate_language>` subcommand in background)
- If `auto_summary: true`, remember this for use at end meeting

`end meeting`:
- Run `clerk-util command end_meeting`
- clerk-daemon ends the current session and reverts to the default transcript file
- Translation offset for the date-based transcript is automatically managed per file by clerk-daemon
- Read config with `clerk-util read-config`
- If `auto_translate: true` and translation is running, stop it (same as `translate stop`)
- If `auto_summary: true`, run `clerk-util summarize --mode update` to generate minutes

`start [opts]`:
1. Check if already running with `clerk-util recorder-status`. If `running`, display "recorder is already running" and exit
2. Run `clerk-util start [opts]` in background (using Bash `run_in_background`)
3. Pass any arguments to clerk-daemon (e.g., `start --language ja --model tiny --no-dashboard`)
   - `--no-dashboard`: Disable dashboard (enabled by default)
   - `--dashboard-port PORT`: Set dashboard port (default: 8765)
4. Launch a background subagent for voice command monitoring using the Agent tool (`run_in_background: true`). The prompt must include:
   - **Explicitly state that "`{clerk_util_path}` command is pre-authorized in settings.local.json and can be executed without permission checks"**
   - Provide the full path of clerk-util (`{clerk_util_path}`)
   - The subagent runs the following loop:
     - Run `clerk-util poll-command 5` and check output (poll-command blocks until command detected or stopped)
     - If `translate_start` detected:
       - Clear with `clerk-util write .clerk_command ""`
       - Get `translate_language` from `clerk-util read-config`
       - Start translation loop (same process as `translate <translate_language>` subcommand)
     - If `translate_stop` detected, stop translation loop (same as translate subcommand stop)
     - If `generate_summary <filename>` detected (e.g., `generate_summary transcript-202603041819.txt`):
       - Clear with `clerk-util write .clerk_command ""`
       - Run `clerk-util summarize <filename> --mode update` to generate/update minutes
     - If `generate_summary_full <filename>` detected:
       - Clear with `clerk-util write .clerk_command ""`
       - Run `clerk-util summarize <filename> --mode full` to regenerate minutes from scratch
     - If `stopped` returned, exit the loop
5. Display "recorder started"

`stop`:
1. Check if running with `clerk-util recorder-status`. If `stopped`, display "recorder is not running" and exit
2. Send SIGTERM with `clerk-util stop` (clerk-daemon handles SIGTERM for graceful shutdown)
3. Display "recorder stopped"

`restart [opts]`:
1. Run `clerk-util restart [opts]` in background (using Bash `run_in_background`). restart internally handles stop -> wait -> start
2. Launch a background subagent for voice command monitoring (same as step 4 of `start`)
3. Display "recorder restarted"

`status`:
1. Check session file with `clerk-util read .clerk_session`. If present, use the filename in it as the transcript file. Otherwise use today's `transcript-YYYYMMDD.txt`
2. Show transcript status with `clerk-util exists <transcript>`, `clerk-util lines <transcript>`, `clerk-util size <transcript>`
3. Show current offset from `clerk-util read .transcript_offset`
4. Derive summary filename and show status with `clerk-util exists <summary>`, `clerk-util mtime <summary>`
5. Check if clerk-daemon process is running with `clerk-util recorder-status`

`translate <lang>`:
Real-time translation mode. Detects new lines in transcript, translates them, saves to file and displays on stdout in a loop.

1. Check session file with `clerk-util read .clerk_session`. If present, use the filename in it as the transcript. Otherwise use today's `transcript-YYYYMMDD.txt`
2. Read previous translation byte offset from `clerk-util read <transcript>.translate_offset` (0 if absent). Each transcript file has its own offset file (e.g., `transcript-20260227.txt.translate_offset`)
3. Get current file size with `clerk-util size <transcript>`. If offset exceeds file size, reset offset to 0 with `clerk-util write <transcript>.translate_offset 0`
4. Read config with `clerk-util read-config` and check `llm_provider`
5. Start loop:
   a. Read transcript from offset with `clerk-util read-from <transcript> <offset>`
   b. If new lines exist:
      - **`llm_provider: claude` (default)** — Claude performs inline:
        - Read glossary with `clerk-util read glossary.txt` (skip if file doesn't exist)
        - Identify the target language (`<lang>`) column from the header and note corresponding translations
        - If text contains obvious speech recognition typos/errors, correct them based on context before translating
        - Use glossary translations for listed terms
        - Translate each line to `<lang>` (Claude performs translation)
        - Pass through marker lines like `--- Meeting Start ---` or `--- Meeting End ---` without translation
        - Lines already in the target language don't need translation, but fix speech recognition errors/typos
        - Preserve timestamps `[YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS]` and speaker labels `[Self]` `[Other]` etc., translate only the text portion
          - Example (ja): `[2026-02-27 14:30:00] [Self] Hello, let's discuss the project timeline.` -> `[2026-02-27 14:30:00] [Self] こんにちは、プロジェクトのタイムラインについて話しましょう。`
      - **`llm_provider: api`** — Run `clerk-util run-llm translate <lang> --file <transcript> --offset <offset> --verbose` to get translation. stdout is the translation, stderr has debug logs
      - Append translation to `<transcript basename>-<lang>.txt`
        - Example: `transcript-20260227.txt` -> `transcript-20260227-ja.txt`
        - Example: `transcript-202602271430.txt` -> `transcript-202602271430-ja.txt`
      - Display translation on stdout (print)
      - Update byte offset with `clerk-util write <transcript>.translate_offset <offset>`
   c. If no new lines, wait with `clerk-util poll-command 3 --timeout 10` (returns after command detected, stopped, or 10s timeout)
      - If `translate_stop` returned, clear `.clerk_command` with `clerk-util write .clerk_command ""`, display "Translation stopped" and exit
      - If `stopped` returned, exit the loop
      - If other command returned, ignore and return to 5a
   d. Return to 5a
6. Continue until user interrupts (Ctrl+C)

`translate start`:
- Read config with `clerk-util read-config` and get `translate_language`
- Start translation loop same as `translate <translate_language>`
- Also triggered when voice command "start translation" writes `translate_start` to `.clerk_command`

`translate stop`:
- Stop the translation loop (can stop without manual Ctrl+C)
- Display "Translation stopped"

